(982, 323, 322, 'Precious Rachael Mallen', 'What a devotion!', '', '2012-10-07 06:18:54'),
(983, 279, 323, 'Polly Muthoni', 'He''s definitely not my ruler. True christians are led by the Spirit of God, and not satan. Because they belong to God - they are sons of God.', '', '2012-10-07 20:38:39'),
(984, 90, 323, 'Daniel Delayapo', 'Hi Amos. Good Question. Jesus has given us all the power and authority which His Father gave to Him. And the Bible says that the devil has been disarmed and has been defeated. Therefore we as the Body of Christ have power over this world. We can change anything in this world. This therefore means that we are the ones who reign. Amen.', '', '2012-10-08 06:15:07'),
(985, 243, 323, 'Amos', 'Thanx.he is Definitely not our ruler. I was so confused when I red this other book called "what does the bible really teaches us" It was say that satan is the ruler of this world, and that verry soon his kingdom will be abolished. But the trueth is he can only rule those who  allow him to do so.so shall it be. Anather thing is that our God is a jelous God. He does not want to share a thing with anyone (the devel ).', '', '2012-10-08 09:12:36'),
(987, 82, 324, 'Kt - Katlego Pelle', 'Amen. Mpho this is very beautiful. Thank you so much for such a teaching. Resting in God is an act of faith, because resting in God allows you to live with the knowledge that all things have been done for you. I''m blessed.', '', '2012-10-09 19:53:35'),
(988, 66, 324, 'Patricia Mthembu', 'Yes, we have come into the rest of God because we are in Christ Jesus.', '', '2012-10-10 05:21:45'),
(989, 156, 324, 'Patience Modise', 'Mpho I hav learnt a lot. Resting in God simply means believing that God has done it all. So there''s actually nothing 2 worry about, there''s nothing to stress about, God our Father has done all things for us and He has given us all things. amen and amen.', '', '2012-10-10 20:56:22'),
(990, 157, 326, 'Nelson', 'Words are powerful, and we all know that right, but if scripture says "...on the day of judgment people will give account for every careless word they speak"? It becomes shocking doesn''t it?? Well, to me in a way it does,and that''s what is recorded in the book of Matthew 12:36', '', '2012-10-10 23:28:22'),
(991, 157, 325, 'Nelson', 'Amen indeed my sister. Though I will not get into the issues of "corporate prayer" and "individual prayer", for now, still I would really like to commend you for the truth and power in your devotion, concerning our privileges as children of the most high God.', '', '2012-10-10 23:35:40'),
(992, 157, 324, 'Nelson', 'Amen and amen. Thank you so much brother Kt as well for underlying for us so brilliantly the act of faith we have to take on our part with the revelation we''ve received.', '', '2012-10-10 23:39:04'),
(993, 279, 327, 'Polly Muthoni', 'But He that said seven days to the horse and said seven days to the tortoise knows how to bring the horse and the tortoise into the ark by the seventh day." - Great teaching right there. That we should at all times rest assured that He that promised is faithful, and that He will see us through difficult challenges, regardless of our strength and physical capabilities.', '', '2012-10-11 15:17:44'),
(994, 196, 327, 'Simon REDEEMED Matlala', 'Wow my brother, I''m so motivated. You have helped 2 be rest assured that even if i don''t know how God will do it, but it will happen. Wow i am so blessed my brother, thank you and God bless you more with knowledge.', '', '2012-10-11 16:45:59'),
(995, 360, 322, 'Keratilwe', 'Beautiful. Acknowledge the Lord your God and your understanding of Gods love will reveale to you his sufficient grace! Amen my Sister', '', '2012-10-11 18:53:25'),
(996, 360, 328, 'Keratilwe', 'Yes through it all He still remains the Loving Almighty Lord!', '', '2012-10-11 18:57:12'),
(997, 307, 328, 'Boitumelo Masuge', 'Amen my sister, we serve a faithful God who is always there for us through thick nd thin.', '', '2012-10-11 19:35:26'),
(998, 307, 322, 'Boitumelo Masuge', 'Amen bretheren, the love of God will never ceases nd his mercies will never come to an end. If we cn love the way God loves us this world will be a better place, but I believe God wl strengthens us to do wat is ryt nd change the world.', '', '2012-10-11 20:09:41'),
(999, 307, 326, 'Boitumelo Masuge', 'Amen ds is powerful Nelson. Wtever we speak wt our lips got power, weather good or bad, is up to us to pronounce only good things cause we will see results. We were given power to build nd to destroy.is up to u which one u use.', '', '2012-10-11 21:06:28'),
(1000, 152, 326, 'Sylvia Molefe', 'Wow, Nelson that is very true. As christians we often forget that creation came to being by "WORD". I belive this will constantly remind us to be careful of what we say. Thanx & stay blessed.', '', '2012-10-12 07:46:10'),
(1001, 152, 328, 'Sylvia Molefe', 'Amen - God is good at all times. I believe we have to know the a knock down is not a knock out. Storms of life mite knock as down but for as long as we stay in the race we will dust ourselves and continue.', '', '2012-10-12 07:51:43'),
(1002, 82, 327, 'Kt - Katlego Pelle', 'Nelson, Once again thank you for sharing such wisdom with us, May the increase His revelation knowledge in you. This devotion has inspired me and it has taught me to hold on to the heart of God even though I cannot understand His mind, meaning that I should hold on to what God has said even though I don''t fully understand the process of how it''s going to unfold. thank you Sir.', '', '2012-10-12 09:51:47'),
(1003, 157, 326, 'Nelson', 'Thank you Sis Sylvia and you too!', '', '2012-10-12 12:21:40'),
(1004, 381, 328, 'Ifetayo Elijah', 'THANK GOD FOR THIS MESSAGE', '', '2012-10-13 09:11:24'),
(1005, 263, 328, 'Moemedi FlowerBoy Romeo Mosiane', 'What a lovely devotion dear,it''s so short and powerful,trust goes with faith,what we have to do,it''s just have faith and put trust in Our God,remain blessed.', '', '2012-10-15 04:23:09'),
(1006, 263, 327, 'Moemedi FlowerBoy Romeo Mosiane', 'What a powerful wakeup devotion,thank you Nelson for this inspiring devotion,we are not living our life Nelson,we are living a pleasing life,this devotion proly tought me that truly, life is not a competition,we live our lives to please others and compete with them but it''s not like that,thank u Nelson,remain blessed my brother.', '', '2012-10-15 04:33:44'),
(1007, 279, 328, 'Polly Muthoni', 'Amen, Just the words i needed this Monday morning, Thanks for the encouraging reminder of God''s word.', '', '2012-10-15 08:34:37'),
(1008, 72, 328, 'Paul Christopher', 'Beautiful devotion my dear, thank you.', '', '2012-10-16 10:04:39'),
(1009, 69, 328, 'Mpho Dlamini', 'Precious, if there was a button for ''Like'', I would click on it. I ''Like'' this devotion. Praise be to Jesus, Amen.', '', '2012-10-16 10:06:37'),
(1010, 69, 329, 'Mpho Dlamini', 'Hallelujah. My trust shall remain in the Lord, I shall not depend on my own understanding. I shall trust in de Lord al the days of my life. Amen.', '', '2012-10-16 10:28:33'),
(1011, 69, 324, 'Mpho Dlamini', 'Thank you very much friends for your comments, I''m so much honoured and blessed.', '', '2012-10-16 13:46:32'),
(1012, 279, 329, 'Polly Muthoni', 'Amen, what an interpretation of the scripture, am truly blessed and encouraged.', '', '2012-10-16 13:54:07'),
(1013, 323, 330, 'Precious Rachael Mallen', 'I hav always thought that de fruits of the Spirit are de fruits of the Holy Spirit, but 2day my understanding has been enlightened. thank you Jesus.', '', '2012-10-17 14:09:58'),
(1014, 82, 332, 'Kt - Katlego Pelle', 'I feel so honoured and highly favoured by God, And now I know how much I mean to Him.', '', '2012-10-18 15:13:40'),
(1015, 307, 330, 'Boitumelo Masuge', 'Wow wat a revelation, amen mphoza this is so true, we need to take care of our spirit so that we may produce good fruits, as it says we will know them by their fruits. We must represent God by the fruits dat we bear.', '', '2012-10-18 16:24:26'),
(1016, 323, 330, 'Precious Rachael Mallen', 'Amen. Well said Boitumelo. God is glorified in de fruits we bear.', '', '2012-10-18 19:50:47'),
(1017, 156, 332, 'Patience Modise', 'OOOHHHH YES, I mean so much to my Father. I have learnt that the reason why God created the earth first before creating me is bcoz He wanted 2 prepare everything for me first. OOOHHH Father, you r so wonderful. Thank you Lord for your Love towards me.', '', '2012-10-18 20:03:47'),
(1018, 156, 330, 'Patience Modise', 'LOL I have always thought dat they are fruits of the Spirit of God. LOL. Mpho thank you for this. The truth is that, there r still many Christians who think dat these fruits are fruits of de Holy spirit of God. I''m so thankful to God that today He has brought this to my understanding. Amen.', '', '2012-10-18 20:06:28'),
(1019, 307, 333, 'Boitumelo Masuge', 'Thank u my brother for the reminder that everything dat I need/want is in the word, all I hv to do is to meditate nd put ds word into practice. Confession being part of it, making/changing what is in the supernatural to be in the natural. Oh wat a Great God we serve, we are blessed indeed.', '', '2012-10-21 05:51:52'),
(1020, 307, 334, 'Boitumelo Masuge', 'Amen amen this is so great Nelson, the annointing of multiplecation. God created us to prosper in everything we do or touch, is up to us how we use these gifts, everything ws made available for us is up to us to use it. Be blessed wt more knowledge.', '', '2012-10-21 05:59:50'),
(1021, 112, 328, 'Joshua Nkoe', 'Thanks my sister for this devotion.We trust in Him, Christ the hope of glory.', '', '2012-10-21 07:47:14'),
(1022, 323, 333, 'Precious Rachael Mallen', 'my brother, I''m motivated & inspired. I am surely going to study Psalm 1 and Deut 28 tonight b4 I sleep. I hav learnt in this devotion that in Christ it is so easy 2 prosper. Actually prosperity is surely our portion.', '', '2012-10-21 17:02:44'),
(1023, 69, 335, 'Mpho Dlamini', 'Amen Sis B, Christ Jesus died to forgive us, so we don''t have to allow the past to have a say in our lives.', '', '2012-10-22 06:21:29'),
(1024, 82, 335, 'Kt - Katlego Pelle', 'Boitumelo I AMEN this devotion. @ the cross, Jesus said "it is finished" (John 19:30). So according to GRACE, all sins are forgiven, even future sins. All we have to do is just to believe that we are forgiven and walk in this faith of the new life Christ has brought us into. Amen.', '', '2012-10-22 06:29:59'),
(1025, 307, 335, 'Boitumelo Masuge', 'Amen indeed it finished, y still hanging to the past. Satan has lost the battle, we shudnt let him to remind us abt wat happened in our past. Jesus has paid it all. Halleluyah we r free.', '', '2012-10-22 07:32:09'),
(1026, 82, 333, 'Kt - Katlego Pelle', 'Thank you once again Nelson for yet another HOT devotion. This devotion reminds me of your previous devotion which I studied "The Mimshack Anointing". Amen. This is the ability we have, to turn whatever we touch into Gold. Whatever we do has to succeed because we are of royalty. Amen!', '', '2012-10-22 09:23:29'),
(1027, 157, 333, 'Nelson', 'It certainly is our portion Rachael. I''m glad it actually reminds you of one of the topics we shared here Kt.And, wow, what can I say to you my sister Boitu but that God bless you more and more and more and more...! :)', '', '2012-10-22 16:26:08'),
(1028, 157, 334, 'Nelson', 'My wonderful lady sis Boitumelo, God dearly bless you and thanks!', '', '2012-10-22 16:27:25'),
(1029, 82, 335, 'Kt - Katlego Pelle', 'Yes Sis Boitumelo, we are FREE indeed. Amen.', '', '2012-10-22 16:38:37'),
(1030, 156, 335, 'Patience Modise', 'Just when I saw the theme of this message, I was blessed already just to be reminded that I am forgiven and that my sins will neva be counted against me.', '', '2012-10-22 16:40:23'),
(1031, 307, 335, 'Boitumelo Masuge', 'True that patience we shud worry no more, all we hav to do is to make things right with God nd put our lives in order.', '', '2012-10-22 17:05:58'),
(1032, 157, 335, 'Nelson', 'Amen. You know, I have to confess, I always come across as having this problem that we as Christians seem to take for granted sometimes the real meaning of the cross: which is to save and redeem humanity of sin and reconcile it with God permanently. And so we tend to get a bit ''comfortable'', convinced that we are forgiven and that the Grace of God is always there to forgive us when we go stray; and then we get soaked in sin; forgetting that sin is sin, and that it is not of God but of God is righteousness, justice and holiness.', '', '2012-10-23 01:27:24'),
(1033, 157, 335, 'Nelson', 'What do you think guys?', '', '2012-10-23 01:28:50'),
(1034, 82, 335, 'Kt - Katlego Pelle', 'Nelson I agree with you. That is the danger of misunderstanding GRACE. Many Christians misunderstand GRACE and think that GRACE is a ticket to live as they want to. That is why people asked the Apostle Paul and said, "Shall we sin so that GRACE may increase?" Apostle Paul answered and said, "NO, by NO means, for we have died to Sin and have been made alive with Christ Jesus". Therefore friends, we need to understand that the fact that we are already forgiven, does not means that we can live as we please, In fact because we are forgiven we should live as forgiven people, And because we are righteous, we should live out this righteousness which Christ gave us as a gift. Somebody shout AMEN ....', '', '2012-10-23 07:19:13'),
(1045, 90, 341, 'Daniel Delayapo', 'My brother Nelson, I love the way you Praise your God. I''m blessed and inspired by the knowledge of the kind of God we belong to. Thank you Lord for allowing us to belong to you and partake in your Divine Nature.', '', '2012-10-26 11:56:51'),
(1036, 243, 117, 'Amos', 'not 4geting God''s mercy. 4 he says I will have mercy on whom ever I choose...God is able. Amen', '', '2012-10-23 17:11:17'),
(1037, 243, 332, 'Amos', 'Ohh my God, this is wonderful. How he loves us. Amen.', '', '2012-10-23 17:18:45'),
(1038, 243, 329, 'Amos', 'Amen. Those who put their trust in God will not be put to shame. His promises are real, and are for us. Ohh,how great is thy word oh Lord. Thank u 4 the devotion.', '', '2012-10-23 17:25:19'),
(1039, 243, 329, 'Amos', 'Amen. Those who put their trust in God will not be put to shame. His promises are real, and are for us. Ohh,how great is thy word oh Lord. Thank u 4 the devotion.', '', '2012-10-23 17:26:19'),
(1040, 243, 331, 'Amos', 'The devil is a lie. I submit my self to God. God is a fighter, he does not wnt our help either. But he only wnts us to submit our selves to him. Thanks to u, and to God 4 his true word which is alive.', '', '2012-10-23 17:38:50'),
(1041, 323, 338, 'Precious Rachael Mallen', 'Nelson my brother I love this devotion But I want to understand here: Is it wrong to have too much wisdom Or what you are saying is dat we should remain childlike even though we possess too much wisdom?? hope i make sense.', '', '2012-10-24 08:10:24'),
(1042, 82, 338, 'Kt - Katlego Pelle', 'Powerful one Nelson. @Precious Rachael, I believe the issue here is too remain childlike even though one possesses great wisdom. It can never be wrong to have great Wisdom. Let''s hear Nelson''s view.', '', '2012-10-24 08:13:11'),
(1043, 82, 340, 'Kt - Katlego Pelle', 'Nina, this is very Powerful. That is why Paul said in Phil 1:29 "What a priviledge it is to suffer for Christ". It''s true, trials develop us and through trials we learn to trust and believe in God more.', '', '2012-10-25 14:56:49'),
(1044, 157, 338, 'Nelson', 'Valid question indeed, Rachael. And no, like brother Kt has put it, it can never be wrong to have great wisdom. Wisdom is a beautiful thing; it''s of God. But conventional wisdom is what popularly eats away the deeper-kind of the knowledge of God, even the fear of God. I hope you understand. (Convectional wisdom (CW) Conventional wisdom (CW) is a term used to describe ideas or explanations that are generally accepted as true by the public or by ''experts''...SOURCE: WIKIPEDIA)', '', '2012-10-26 03:09:13'),
(1046, 82, 341, 'Kt - Katlego Pelle', 'Even before ''there'' was ''there'', He was THERE, lol I love that Man. I''m humbled that such a great God chose to make me like Him. Amen.', '', '2012-10-26 11:58:47'),
(1047, 157, 341, 'Nelson', 'MAJOR!! THIS A MAJOR GOD.', '', '2012-10-27 07:56:58'),
